table.name: MD_ADDITIONAL_PROPERTIES
table.Comment: This table is used to store additional properties in key-value pairs. It is designed to store "other information" that is not supported in the main database object table.

table.name: MD_CATALOGS
table.Comment: Store catalogs in this table.

table.name: MD_COLUMNS
table.Comment: Column information is stored in this table.

table.name: MD_CONNECTIONS
table.Comment: This table is used to store connection information. For example, in migrations, we could be carrying out a consolidation which occurs across many connections.

table.name: MD_CONSTRAINTS
table.Comment: Table for storing information about a constraint

table.name: MD_CONSTRAINT_DETAILS
table.Comment: Constraint details show what columns are "involved" in a constraint.

table.name: MD_DERIVATIVES
table.Comment: This table is used to store objects that are derived from each other. For example in a migration an auto-increment column in a source model could be mapped to a primary key, and a sequence, and a trigger. The MD_DERIVATIVES table would store the fact that these 3 objects are derived from the auto-increment column.

table.name: MD_GROUPS
table.Comment: Groups of users in a schema

table.name: MD_GROUP_MEMBERS
table.Comment: This table is used to store the members of a group.

table.name: MD_GROUP_PRIVILEGES
table.Comment: This table stores the privileges granted to a group (or role)

table.name: MD_INDEXES
table.Comment: This table is used to store information about the indexes in a schema

table.name: MD_INDEX_DETAILS
table.Comment: This table stores the details of an index. It shows what columns are "part" of the index.

table.name: MD_OTHER_OBJECTS
table.Comment: For storing objects that don't belong anywhere else

table.name: MD_PACKAGES
table.Comment: For storing packages

table.name: MD_PRIVILEGES
table.Comment: This table stores privilege information

table.name: MD_PROJECTS
table.Comment: This is a top level container for a set of connections.

table.name: MD_REGISTRY
table.Comment: Table to store information on the MD_ repository. This lists the objects to be dropped if you wish to remove the repository

table.name: MD_REPOVERSIONS
table.Comment: This table is used to version this schema for future requirements.

table.name: MD_SCHEMAS
table.Comment: This is the holder for schemas

table.name: MD_SEQUENCES
table.Comment: For storing information on sequences.

table.name: MD_STORED_PROGRAMS
table.Comment: Container for stored programs.

table.name: MD_SYNONYMS
table.Comment: For storing synonym information.

table.name: MD_TABLES
table.Comment: Table used to store information about tables.

table.name: MD_TABLESPACES
table.Comment: For storing information about tablespaces.

table.name: MD_TRIGGERS
table.Comment: For storing information about triggers.

table.name: MD_USERS
table.Comment: User information.

table.name: MD_USER_DEFINED_DATA_TYPES
table.Comment: For sotring information on user defined data types.

table.name: MD_USER_PRIVILEGES
table.Comment: This table stores privileges granted to individual users

table.name: MD_VIEWS
table.Comment: For storing information on views.

table.name: MIGR_DATATYPE_TRANSFORM_MAP
table.Comment: Table for storing data type maps. A map is simply a collection of rules

table.name: POI_ADDRESS_BASE

table.Comment: erp

table.name: SYJD_ERP_ORDER_ITEM
table.Comment: erp

view.Comment: View to iterate over all views in the system
